WEBVTT

00:00.457 --> 00:02.947
(narrator) Previously on "The
Making of the Mob: Chicago"...

00:03.058 --> 00:04.707
They say I violate the Prohibition law.

00:04.709 --> 00:05.996
Who doesn't?

00:06.101 --> 00:08.794
(narrator) After rising to the
top of the Chicago underworld

00:08.796 --> 00:12.548
and evading the law
for more than a decade,

00:12.550 --> 00:15.167
the government closes in on Al Capone

00:15.169 --> 00:16.834
using a two-pronged attack.

00:17.888 --> 00:19.388
One led by Eliot Ness...

00:19.390 --> 00:21.173
Prohibition Bureau!

00:21.175 --> 00:23.592
(narrator) The other by the IRS.

00:23.594 --> 00:25.227
I want to nail this son of a bitch.

00:25.229 --> 00:27.012
(narrator) With the law moving in,

00:27.014 --> 00:29.431
Capone spirals out of control.

00:29.433 --> 00:32.433
I want him taken care of, and
I want you to do it now.

00:32.436 --> 00:36.572
(narrator) Soon he's
indicted and brought to trial,

00:36.574 --> 00:39.775
not for the violent
crimes he's committed,

00:39.777 --> 00:41.243
but for tax evasion.

00:41.245 --> 00:43.328
(judge) Court finds the defendant guilty

00:43.330 --> 00:45.330
on five counts.

00:45.332 --> 00:48.617
(narrator) The kingpin is sentenced
to 11 years in federal prison.

00:48.619 --> 00:51.620
They got me locked up
like a caged animal in here.

00:51.622 --> 00:55.257
(narrator) Now it's up to
Al Capone's inner circle

00:55.259 --> 00:57.459
to save his empire.

01:00.398 --> 01:03.382
♪ ♪

01:31.353 --> 01:35.725
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
